      • setID

        public boolean setID(java.lang.String id)
              throws java.lang.NullPointerException
        Sets the user id if the user is currently invalid and doesn't have an id yet. If the user is valid and has an id, then we do nothing. If the input id is null, empty, or we have a valid user with no id, we throw a NullPointerException.
        Parameters:
        id - - Unique string identifier for the User
        Returns:
        boolean - true if id is set, false if not
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException
